HI Chuck,

How is everything? I got a chance to change my fuel filter today and 
unfortunately I am still experiencing the same problem.
My bus starts, runs, and then dies about 30 seconds after. I can immediately 
restart and the same is repeated.
I have a fresh air filter, fuel filter, head temperature sensor, and plugs. 
I am also pretty sure there are no vacuum leaks.

When I took off the old fuel filter there was some rust and dirt in the 
filter. Nothing too extreme though.  I was hoping that the new filter would 
make a difference. It did not.

I am at a loss here. I seriously thought the problem would be solved. After 
I started the van and let it die I checked my spark plugs. They were bone 
dry. It's obvious that there is no fuel reaching the engine when it dies. 
Any other suggestions?

Thanks,

Matt


